abstract: >-
  NarDialPy is a Python package for building and running
  narrative-driven, structured dialog systems for social
  robots and conversational agents. Conversations are
  authored declaratively as JSON files describing dialogs,
  made up of ordered moves, that can be sequenced through
  dependencies, session agendas, and topic tracking, while
  the runtime handles session flow, branching logic,
  personalization, and screen output. A ConversationAgent
  bridges this dialog logic to concrete text-to-speech,
  speech recognition, large language model, and motion
  services on a chosen device, with pluggable providers for
  platforms such as Pepper, NAO, Alphamini, and desktop
  agents, and for services including Google Cloud,
  ElevenLabs, Dialogflow, and OpenAI. Dialog types range
  from fully scripted functional and narrative dialogs to
  free-form large-language-model-driven exchanges, allowing
  structured and generative interaction styles to be
  combined within a single session. The package builds on
  the Social Interaction Cloud framework and is intended to
  let researchers and developers author the content and
  branching logic of multi-turn, social-robot conversations
  without reimplementing the underlying dialog-management
  runtime for each study or application.
